public CharacterSprite()
Default Constructor for the Sprite. Creates a blank Sprite at location (-1, -1) with a null representation.

CharacterSprite

public CharacterSprite(java.lang.Character c,
                       int x,
                       int y,
                       int layer)
Default Character based sprite. The sprites representation is based on the char object passed in. The Sprite created from the character will be Color.blue in color and have the property of Font.MONOSPACED, Font.PLAIN and have a size of 24. the resulting Sprite will be 30px by 30px.

Parameters:
object - - The Sprite's pictorial representation
x - - X coordinate the Sprite will be set to.
y - - Y coordinate the Sprite will be set to.
layer - - The layer the Sprite resides on. (0 is lowest layer)

CharacterSprite

public CharacterSprite(java.lang.Character c,
                       int x,
                       int y,
                       int layer,
                       int size)
Default Character based sprite. The sprites representation is based on the char object passed in. The Sprite created from the character will be Color.blue in color and have the property of Font.MONOSPACED, Font.PLAIN and have a size of 24. the resulting Sprite will be 30px by 30px. If a size of -1 is specified, then the resulting BufferedImage will not be resized.

Parameters:
c - - the Sprite's pictorial representation.
x - - X coordinate the Sprite will be set to.
y - - Y coordinate the Sprite will be set to.
layer - - The layer the Sprite resides on. (0 is the lowest layer)
size - - The resulting size of the Sprite

CharacterSprite

public CharacterSprite(java.lang.String s,
                       int x,
                       int y,
                       int layer)
Creates a new CharacterSprite which embodies the given String. The resulting BufferedImage will not be resized.

Parameters:
s - - The String the CharacterSprite will represent.
x - - The X location of the CharacterSprite.
y - - The Y location of the CharacterSprite.
layer - - The Layer the CharacterSprite will be located on.
